{"title_page": "Now or Never (Brett Kissel album)", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = Now or Never\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Brett Kissel]]\n| cover        = Now or Never Brett Kissel.png\n| alt          = \n| released     = {{Start date|2020|01|01}}\n| recorded     = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Country music|Country]]\n| length       = {{duration|m=51|s=11}}\n| label        = [[Warner Music Canada]] / BAK 2 BAK Entertainment Inc.\n| producer     = {{hlist|Bart McKay|Jacob Durrett|Brett Kissel|Luke Wooten}}\n| prev_title   = [[We Were That Song]]\n| prev_year    = 2017\n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Now or Never\n | type        = Studio\n | single1     = Drink About Me\n | single1date = September 6, 2019\n | single2     = She Drives Me Crazy \n | single2date = February 1, 2020<ref>{{cite web |url=https://canadianbeats.ca/2020/02/01/brett-kissel-releases-new-single-and-video-she-drives-me-crazy/|title=Brett Kissel releases new single and video, \u201cShe Drives Me Crazy\u201d|date=February 1, 2020|first=Dutch|last=Bickell|work=Canadian Beats Media}}</ref>\n\n}}\n}}\n'''''Now or Never''''' is the fourth studio album by Canadian [[country music]] singer [[Brett Kissel]]. It was released on January 1, 2020 via [[Warner Music Canada]]. \n\n==Content==\n\"Now or Never\" features eight tracks in total including Kissel's debut American single \"Drink About Me\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.soundslikenashville.com/news/brett-kissel-drink-about-me-introduction/|title=Canadian Cowboy Brett Kissel Rides into the United States with \u2018Drink About Me\u2019|date=September 17, 2019|first=Kelly|last=Dearmore|work=Sounds Like Nashville}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://daily.plaympe.com/brett-kissel-drink-about-me/|title=Brett Kissel \u2013 Drink About Me|date=September 6, 2019 |work=Daily Play MPE|publisher=Destiny Media Technologies}}</ref> Kissel noted how he incorporated tracks of different styles between [[Neotraditional country|traditional country]], [[Canadian country music|Canadian country]], and [[Country pop|pop country]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/ca/album/now-or-never/1477373558|title=Now or Never - Brett Kissel|date=January 1, 2020|work=[[Apple Music]]}}</ref> Kissel stated that some songs found \"a new direction\" while others took him in \"the direction of his roots\", and that the album has \"something for everybody\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.soundslikenashville.com/music/brett-kissel-new-years-now-or-never-album/|title=Brett Kissel Plots New Year\u2019s Release of 'Now Or Never' Album|date=December 24, 2019||first=Chris||last=Parton|work=Sounds Like Nashville}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n|headline = ''Now or Never'' track listing\n| title1 = Drink About Me\n| length1 = 3:11\n| writer1 = {{hlist|Ben Stennis|[[Matt Rogers]]}}\n| title2 = A Few Good Stories\n| length2 = 2:45\n| writer2 = {{hlist|[[Ben Hayslip]]|[[Christopher Stevens (musician)|Chris Stevens]]|[[Rhett Akins]]}}\n| title3 = That's Country Music\n| length3 = 4:16\n| writer3 = {{hlist|[[Brett Kissel]]|Karen Kosowski|Phil Barton}}\n| title4 = Young Enough\n| length4 = 3:21\n| writer4 = {{hlist|[[David Hodges]]|[[Jessi Alexander]]|Will Weatherly}}\n| title5 = She Drives Me Crazy\n| length5 = 3:04\n| writer5 = {{hlist|Kissel|[[Emma-Lee|Emma-Lee Doty]]|Kosowski}}\n| title6 = Hummingbird\n| length6 = 2:57\n| writer6 = {{hlist|Kissel|Doty|Kosowski}}\n| title7 = I'm Not Him, I'm Not Her \n| note7 = featuring Christina Taylor\n| length7 = 3:52\n| writer7 = {{hlist|Kissel}}\n| title8 = Coffee With Her\n| length8 = 2:42\n| writer8 = {{hlist|Daniel Ross|Hodges|Laura Veltz}}\n| total_length = 26:04\n}}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+Sales chart performance for ''Now or Never''\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardCanada|43|artist=Brett Kissel|ro