 = HALO\n| background      = group_or_band\n| image           = Idol group \u2018HALO\u2019 members arrive at the red carpet event of the Puchon International Fantastic Film Festival in Bucheon on July 17, 2014.jpg\n| landscape       = yes\n| caption         = \n| alias           = Hexagon of Absolute Light and Organization\n| origin          = [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]]\n| genre           = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[Dance-pop]]|[[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]}}\n| years_active    = {{start date|2014}}\u20132019\n| label           = Histar Entertainment\n| associated_acts = \n| website         = \n| current_members = \n* Dino\n* Inhaeng\n* Ooon\n* [[Kim Jae-yong|Jaeyong]]\n* Heecheon\n* Yoondong\n}}\n\n'''HALO''' ([[Hangul]]: \ud5e4\uc77c\ub85c; abbreviation for '''Hexagon of Absolute Light and Organization''') is a South Korean [[Boy band|boy group]] formed by Histar Entertainment in [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/272908|title=\uc2e0\uc778\uadf8\ub8f9 \ud5e4\uc77c\ub85c, \ub2e8\uccb4 \ud2f0\uc800 \uacf5\uac1c \u2018\uccb4\uc628\uc774 \ub728\uac70\uc6cc\u2019|publisher=Ten Asia|language=Korean}}</ref> The group consists of six members: Dino, Inhaeng, Ooon, [[Kim Jae-yong|Jaeyong]], Heecheon and Yoondong.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&sm=tab_ppn&query=%EA%B0%80%EC%88%98%ED%97%A4%EC%9D%BC%EB%A1%9C&os=1984361&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService|title=\ud5e4\uc77c\ub85c \ud504\ub85c\ud544|publisher=Naver|language=ko}}</ref> They debuted on June 26, 2014, with the single \"Fever\".\n\n==History==\n\nOn May 8, 2019, HALO's contract with Histar Entertainment ended.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://news.kstyle.com/article.ksn?articleNo=2116673 | title=HALO\u3001\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u5168\u54e1\u304c\u5951\u7d04\u6e80\u4e86\u2026\u4e8b\u52d9\u6240\u304c\u516c\u5f0f\u30b3\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8\u300c\u4eca\u5f8c\u306e\u6d3b\u52d5\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066\u306f\u8b70\u8ad6\u4e2d\u300d | language=ja | work=TV Report | publisher=KStyle | date=2019-05-08 | accessdate=2019-10-11}}</ref> Following the news, Heecheon, Youndoung, and Ooon (under his real name, Jeong Young-hoon) became participants in the reality competition series ''[[Produce 101 Japan]]''.<ref>{{cite news | first=Jin-ri | last=Jang | url=http://www.spotvnews.co.kr/?mod=news&act=articleView&idxno=314138 | title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5]\ud5e4\uc77c\ub85c \uc624\uc6b4-\uc724\ub3d9-\ud76c\ucc9c, '\ud504\ub85c\ub4c0\uc2a4101' \uc77c\ubcf8\ud310 \ucd9c\uc5f0\u2026'\uc7ac\ub370\ubdd4 \ub3c4\uc804'  | language=ko | work=Spot News | date=2019-09-02 | accessdate=2019-09-03}}</ref> However, all members left the show prior to its finale, citing personal reasons.<ref name=\"huffpo 2019-12-05\">{{cite news | first=Aya | last=Ikuta | url=https://www.huffingtonpost.jp/entry/produce101_jp_5de8adede4b0d50f32ae77db | title=\u300cPRODUCE 101 JAPAN\u300d\u97d3\u56fd\u306e\u53c2\u52a0\u8005\u304c\u76f8\u6b21\u3044\u3067\u8f9e\u9000\u3057\u30010\u4eba\u306b\u3002\u904b\u55b6\u304cSNS\u306e\u8ab9\u8b17\u4e2d\u50b7\u306b\u30de\u30ca\u30fc\u547c\u3073\u304b\u3051 | language=ja | work=[[The Huffington Post]] | date=2019-12-05 | accessdate=2019-12-05}}</ref>\n\n==Members==\n* Dino ([[Hangul]]: \ub514\ub178)\n* Inhaeng (\uc778\ud589)\n* Ooon (\uc624\uc6b4)\n* [[Kim Jae-yong|Jaeyong]] (\uc7ac\uc6a9)\n* Heecheon (\ud76c\ucc9c)\n* Yoondong (\uc724\ub3d9)\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:25em;\" | Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\" style=\"width:5em;\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Sales\n|-\n! <small>[[Oricon|JPN]]</small><br><ref>{{cite web|script-title=ja:HALO\u306e\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u4f5c\u54c1|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/666497/products/album/|website=Oricon Style|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=