onio]]*\n|Jaguars ||[[San Antonio]] || [[Texas]] || [[Red River Athletic Conference]]\n|-\n!scope=row| [[Westcliff University]]\n|Warriors ||[[Irvine, California|Irvine]] || [[California]] || [[California Pacific Conference]]\n|}\n*Texas A&M\u2013San Antonio \u2013 adding basketball in 2022.\n\n==See also==\n\n*[[List of NCAA Division I institutions]]\n*[[List of NCAA Division II institutions]]\n*[[List of NCAA Division III institutions]]\n*[[List of USCAA institutions]]\n*[[List of NCCAA institutions]]\n*[[List of NAIA football programs]]\n*[[NAIA lacrosse]]\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{National Association of Intercollegiate Athletics}}\n\n[[Category:National Association of Intercollegiate Athletics|Institutions]]\n[[Category:Lists of universities and colleges in the United States|*]]\n[[Category:College sports in the United States lists|NAIA Institutions]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThe [[National Association of Intercollegiate Athletics]] has 249 member colleges and universities for athletic competition.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.naia.org/conferences/files/2019-20_NAIA_Schools_By_Conference.pdf|title=2019-20 NAIA Member Institutions by Conference|website=naia.org|publisher=NAIA}}</ref>\n\n==NAIA institutions==\n\n*'''Note:''' The NAIA once had basketball teams split into two divisions. The association discontinued its Division II basketball championships for both men and women after the 2019\u201320 season,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.naia.org/membership/2017-18/releases/20180416fywgr|title=NAIA to Combine Basketball Divisions|date=April 16, 2018|website=NAIA|accessdate=September 7, 2019}}</ref> when the 2020 championships were canceled following a [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|coronavirus pandemic]]. Non-basketball playing institutions are denoted by *.\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ List of NAIA institutions\n!School\n!Nickname\n!City\n!State/<br>Province\n!Conference\